- "high item recommendation coverage" means coverage greater than 80%; 
- "average error per user" refers to the average RMSE by user;
- "from the most inaccurate to the most accurate" corresponds to ordering by average RMSE by user in descending order.

sql:
SELECT MAX(n_good) AS max_n_good
FROM performance_metrics
WHERE n_attempted > 100;

SELECT test_time
FROM performance_metrics
WHERE model_id = 1;

SELECT rmse_by_user
FROM performance_metrics
WHERE ndcg = (SELECT MAX(ndcg) FROM performance_metrics);
